[size=5][b]Companion Perks Stay - (ESPless with TTW Support)[/b][/size]

A lightweight, plugin-free mod that permanently retains companion perks after dismissal. Once you've recruited a companion and earned their perk, it stays, even after they leave your party.

[b][color=#ff0000]⚠️ WARNING:[/color][/b] This mod is ESPless and does not edit any scripts, so dismissing companions will still show the perk-loss popup. The script automatically restores the perk afterward.

[color=#f1c232]NOTE: [/color][color=#ffffff]Some perks after the companion has left make no sense as it relies of dialogue options but who doesn't like collecting them all.[/color]
[line]

[size=4][b]Features[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Permanent Perks[/b] — Companion perks (Spotter, Whiskey Rose, Enhanced Sensors, etc.) are retained after dismissal.[/*]
[*][b]ESPless[/b] — No .esp or .esm required. Does not use a plugin slot.[/*]
[*][b]Zero Performance Impact[/b] — Each companion is checked via a tiny, independent callback every ~1 second.[/*]
[*][b]Safe & Clean[/b] — Install or uninstall at any point without corrupting saves.[/*]
[*][b]Full DLC Support[/b] — Dead Money, Honest Hearts, Lonesome Road companions included.[/*]
[*][b]Full TTW Support[/b] — All 8 Fallout 3 companions (Dogmeat, Jericho, Charon, Fawkes, Clover, Cross, RL-3, Butch) supported.[/*]
[*][b]Branching Quest Perks[/b] — Tracks story-completion perks for Cass, Veronica, Raul, and both ED-E forms.[/*]
[*][b]Smart Notifications[/b] — Shows a corner message when a perk is retained. Uses B42 Notify if installed, falls back to MessageEx otherwise.[/*]
[*][b]INI Configurable[/b] — Toggle notifications and adjust check intervals.[/*]
[*][b]Built-in Test Mode[/b] — Arms all retention flags, strips companion perks, then waits for CPS to restore them and prints a PASS/FAIL result for all 30 perks. Enable via the INI.[/*]
[/list]

[line]

