[line]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[b]Mod Manager (Recommended):[/b]
[list=1]
[*]Download and install using Mod Organizer 2 or Vortex.[/*]
[*]Enable the mod. No load order sorting needed, there is no ESP.[/*]
[/list]

[b]Manual:[/b]
[list=1]
[*]Extract the archive into your Fallout New Vegas [font=Courier New]Data[/font] folder.[/*]
[/list]

[line]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

Edit [font=Courier New]config/CompanionPerksStay.ini[/font]:

[code]
[Settings]
; Show corner notifications when a perk is retained (1 = on, 0 = off)
bShowNotifications = 1

; Frames between perk checks (300 = ~5 seconds at 60 FPS)
iCheckInterval = 300

[Testing]
; Run the built-in perk retention test (set to 1, load save, check console with ~)
; Arms all AuxVars, strips perks, waits for CPS to restore them, then prints PASS/FAIL.
; Set back to 0 to reset.
bTestMode = 0[/code]

[line]

[size=4][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Compatible with [b]all[/b] companion mods (including JIP Companions Command & Control).[/*]
[*]Compatible with all perk overhauls and gameplay mods.[/*]
[*]Fully compatible with Tale of Two Wastelands and all official DLCs.[/*]
[*]No ESP means no plugin conflicts and no load order concerns.[/*]
[/list]

[line]

[size=4][b]Uninstallation[/b][/size]
Simply disable or delete the mod. No save cleaning required, auxiliary variables are automatically cleared on the next save load.

